==English==

===Etymology===
From Old French ''[[pincil]]'' (modern ''[[pinceau]]'' ‘paintbrush’), from a diminutive of Latin ''[[peniculus]]'' ‘brush’, diminutive of Latin ''[[penis]]'' ‘tail’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/pɛnsəl/}}
* {{audio|en-us-pencil.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɛnsəl|-ɛnsəl]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{obsolete}} A [[paintbrush]].
# Writing utensil that uses [[graphite]] (commonly referred to as [[lead]]). Regular pencils usually have a graphite shaft surrounded by wood. A pencil sharpener is used to cut away the wood and leave a fine tip on the pencil. Also available in a [[mechanical]] version where the graphite length can be adjusted and sharpening is not needed......a sharp pointy object[[lol]]

